* ============================================================
*  PINOCCHIO SEEK FIX PROOF (Phase 1.3c)
*
*  Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION. READ-ONLY (no mutation).
*  Purpose: Prove the keyed range-seek fix in cmd_seek.cpp: an ascending SEEK on
*           the active CDX tag now uses LMDB MDB_SET_RANGE (O(log n)) instead of a
*           linear index walk. A near-LAST key was ~57 s on ENROLL (5.5M) and
*           ~16.6 s on STUDENTS (1M) before the fix; it should now be ~ms.
*
*  CORRECTNESS (must be identical to the pre-fix linear walk):
*    ENROLL  SEEK 50999999 -> Found at 5501354
*    STUDENTS SEEK 50999999 -> Found at 1000000
*    descending SEEK 50000000 -> Found at 8   (fallback path, unchanged)
*    SEEK 59999999 (no such SID) -> not found
*    SEEK ANDERSON on LNAME tag -> first Anderson
*
*  RUN (host):
*    powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File .\dottalkpp\data\scripts\pinocchio\run_pinocchio_seek_proof_teed.ps1
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK OFF

SET PATH DBF DBF/pinocchio
SET PATH INDEXES INDEXES/pinocchio
SET PATH LMDB LMDB/pinocchio

ECHO ############################################################
ECHO # ENROLL (5,501,358) -- ascending SEEK on tag SID
ECHO ############################################################
SELECT 1
USE ENROLL
SET INDEX TO ENROLL
SET ORDER TO TAG SID

ECHO === S1. SEEK first key 50000000 (baseline; was already fast) ===
SEEK 50000000
ECHO === S2. SEEK near-LAST key 50999999 (was ~57 s; expect ~ms, Found at 5501354) ===
SEEK 50999999
ECHO === S3. SEEK middle key 50500000 (Found at the first recno with that SID) ===
SEEK 50500000
ECHO === S4. SEEK 59999999 (no such SID; expect not found, fast) ===
SEEK 59999999
ECHO === S5. descending SEEK 50000000 (now KEYED too; expect FAST, Found at 1) ===
ECHO       (was ~67 s AND Found at 8; keyed seek lands on the smallest-recno
ECHO        duplicate -> 1, consistent with ascending. Unique keys unaffected.)
DESCEND
SEEK 50000000
ASCEND

ECHO ############################################################
ECHO # STUDENTS (1,000,000) -- ascending SEEK on SID and LNAME
ECHO ############################################################
SELECT 0
USE STUDENTS
SET INDEX TO STUDENTS
SET ORDER TO TAG SID

ECHO === S6. SEEK near-LAST 50999999 (was ~16.6 s; expect ~ms, Found at 1000000) ===
SEEK 50999999
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 1
ECHO === S7. SEEK char tag: LNAME = ANDERSON (keyed seek on a character key) ===
SET ORDER TO TAG LNAME
SEEK ANDERSON
SMARTLIST SID,LNAME,FNAME NEXT 1

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO SEEK FIX PROOF COMPLETE. Confirm:
ECHO   S2 / S6 ELAPSED collapsed from tens of seconds to milliseconds.
ECHO   Correctness: ENROLL 50999999 -> 5501354 ; STUDENTS 50999999 -> 1000000 ;
ECHO     59999999 -> not found ; ANDERSON -> first Anderson (655360).
ECHO   CHANGED (intended): descending 50000000 -> 1 (was 8) -- smallest-recno
ECHO     duplicate, now consistent with ascending; and FAST (was ~67 s).
ECHO ============================================================
